<p>Britain’s domestic intelligence service, MI5, has alerted parliamentarians that Chinese agents have been contacting U.K. lawmakers and parliamentary staff via LinkedIn while posing as recruiters or headhunters to gather information and influence activity, a warning circulated this week to MPs and staff. The notice prompted senior ministers to urge wider public vigilance and reporting of suspicious online approaches, with the defence minister saying ordinary citizens should heed the warning. Beijing has denied the accusations, and the alert arrives as ministers prepare to consider a decision related to a new Chinese embassy in the U.K..</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/vbC4HW-78oteQPModXFAXjTpOv-c7oA9BHjua4EiJPHeGR8lecG_fc5hd9iJSBFPR1jIDo0HysslPTJQoBqkP4JnfTrxQJY-NOj3cEpAitCoG52HCQ_9syuzrg1VWVuBmKQETbuNFWZX8cUushvz-WkcZ0mf73krPB4RhyQx_mq29owIAW7JmUWuG8rYEApRY4IEgfvTsO2EwRU2X6Cdfg' alt='The Houses of Parliament in London; British security officials warned of targeted approaches to lawmakers.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tactics used: MI5 says operatives posed as headhunters and used cover companies on LinkedIn to make plausible career approaches designed to extract information and influence targets</li><li>Senior reaction: British security minister Dan Jarvis described the activity as a &#x27;covert and calculated&#x27; attempt to gather intelligence and MI5 issued the alert directly to parliamentarians</li><li>Public warning: Defence minister Luke Pollard told the public the parliamentary alert should be heeded by ordinary citizens and urged people to be cautious about unsolicited online contact</li><li>Diplomatic timing: The MI5 notice comes weeks before the government must decide whether to approve a new Chinese embassy site, adding diplomatic sensitivity to the security warning</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>MI5 / UK security minister: MI5 issued a warning to parliamentarians that China was using headhunters to gather intelligence from lawmakers and parliamentary staff members. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/18/world/europe/chinese-spies-linkedin-uk.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>Chinese government: Beijing denies the claim that Chinese agents are targeting U.K. lawmakers via LinkedIn. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/18/britains-mi5-warns-lawmakers-over-chinese-spies-posing-as-headhunters'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>UK defence minister: Luke Pollard said the warning to parliament should be heeded by ordinary citizens and urged caution about online contact. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/19/watch-out-online-contact-chinese-spies-uk-defence-minister-warns-public'>The Guardian</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/chinese-spies-are-trying-to-reach-uk-lawmakers-via-linkedin-mi5-warns'>Chinese spies are trying to reach UK lawmakers via LinkedIn, MI5 warns</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/18/world/europe/chinese-spies-linkedin-uk.html'>Chinese Spies Are Using LinkedIn to Target U.K. Lawmakers, MI5 Warns</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/mi5-spy-service-warns-uk-lawmakers-chinese-spies-posing-as-headhunters1'>MI5 spy service warns UK lawmakers Chinese spies posing as headhunters</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/18/britains-mi5-warns-lawmakers-over-chinese-spies-posing-as-headhunters'>Britain’s MI5 warns lawmakers over Chinese spies posing as ‘headhunters’</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/19/watch-out-online-contact-chinese-spies-uk-defence-minister-warns-public'>Watch out for online contact with Chinese spies, UK defence minister warns public</a> - theguardian.com</li></ul>